WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.780
Here, at the edge of the world, a writer finds her other half dying.

2
00:00:07.640 --> 00:00:13.460
The great dragon Viridian, who scales once held the light of deep forests,

3
00:00:14.280 --> 00:00:16.760
now lies fevered and fading.

4
00:00:17.460 --> 00:00:20.000
His breath is smoke and ruin.

5
00:00:20.980 --> 00:00:26.280
Kalen sees not just a sickness in his body, but a fading in his soul,

6
00:00:26.280 --> 00:00:29.640
a color leaching from their shared sky.

7
00:00:30.360 --> 00:00:35.060
This is an ancient melody, one that whispers of an ending.

8
00:00:35.820 --> 00:00:40.040
But she is a writer. They do not accept endings.

9
00:00:40.540 --> 00:00:48.460
In the archives of Forgotten Lore, she finds a whisper, not of a cure but of a source.

10
00:00:49.580 --> 00:00:55.940
The shrine of Ethelgard, they called it, a place where the mountains own heart beats,

11
00:00:56.700 --> 00:01:02.020
where the ancient power that gave dragons their fire can mend what is broken.

12
00:01:02.980 --> 00:01:10.860
It is a legend, a myth told to hatchlings, but legends are built on the bones of truth,

13
00:01:11.580 --> 00:01:17.840
and Karen has nothing left to believe in, but truth and a dying dragon.

14
00:01:18.340 --> 00:01:26.360
The path to the shrine does not begin with a climb, but a descent into blight.

15
00:01:27.180 --> 00:01:33.280
The whisper would stand before them, a forest sick with its own ancient fever.

16
00:01:34.180 --> 00:01:38.180
The trees twist not in growth, but in pain.

17
00:01:39.180 --> 00:01:44.740
Here, the air itself is a poison, and every shadow seems to reach.

18
00:01:45.700 --> 00:01:49.660
For a healthy dragon, this wood is a challenge.

19
00:01:50.520 --> 00:01:57.540
For Veridian, each step is a battle against the very land that seeks to claim his fading light.

20
00:01:58.040 --> 00:02:04.060
The wood keeps its own secrets, and not all of them are trees.

21
00:02:05.380 --> 00:02:12.640
The dragon hunters move through the gloom like race, their armor scuffed, their weapons stained.

22
00:02:13.640 --> 00:02:17.680
They smell sickness, they smell opportunity.

23
00:02:19.180 --> 00:02:25.400
Kalen's heart hammers against her ribs. Viridian cannot but he can barely stand.

24
00:02:26.120 --> 00:02:30.000
She becomes a shadow guiding him from bolder to hollow,

25
00:02:30.560 --> 00:02:36.100
praying the corrupted forest that seeks to drain him will also hide him,

26
00:02:36.540 --> 00:02:40.120
from those who wish to spill his last drop of life.

27
00:02:40.620 --> 00:02:46.980
The bond between writer and dragon is more than a saddle and a shared sky.

28
00:02:47.720 --> 00:02:49.760
It is a thread of the soul.

29
00:02:50.640 --> 00:02:57.080
And now, Kaelin pulls upon that thread, not for flight, but for life.

30
00:02:57.760 --> 00:03:03.180
She pours her own warmth, her own energy into her dying friend.

31
00:03:03.760 --> 00:03:07.040
It is agony, a hollowing sensation.

32
00:03:07.920 --> 00:03:14.000
But for a moment, a single scale remembers its green, a flicker.

33
00:03:14.640 --> 00:03:20.140
Enough, it is always enough to take one more step toward hope.

34
00:03:20.640 --> 00:03:26.880
They leave the sickness of the forest below, only to meet the fury of the mountain.

35
00:03:27.580 --> 00:03:30.880
The storm-crust does not welcome pilgrims.

36
00:03:31.300 --> 00:03:35.880
It guards its secrets with claws of stone and breath of hurricane.

37
00:03:36.720 --> 00:03:44.920
The wind screams a physical wall of force that seeks to tear them from the cliff and cast them into oblivion.

38
00:03:45.640 --> 00:03:51.840
This is not a path. It is a test, a trial of will against the raw,

39
00:03:52.180 --> 00:03:54.220
unfeeling power of the world.

40
00:03:54.720 --> 00:03:57.200
The mountains will is clear.

41
00:03:58.080 --> 00:03:59.420
Turn back.

42
00:04:00.580 --> 00:04:06.040
A blast of wind, cold and malicious, strikes like a battering ram.

43
00:04:07.160 --> 00:04:08.480
Kalen is gone.

44
00:04:09.340 --> 00:04:12.660
Her world a dizzying spin toward the abyss.

45
00:04:13.520 --> 00:04:16.540
Then a shadow falls over her.

46
00:04:17.280 --> 00:04:23.400
Viridian, her dying friend, extends a wing not for flight, but for sacrifice.

47
00:04:23.400 --> 00:04:31.580
He becomes her shield, his body screaming in protest as he absorbs the theory meant for them both.

48
00:04:32.100 --> 00:04:33.540
He does not fly.

49
00:04:34.280 --> 00:04:37.240
He endures for her.

50
00:04:37.740 --> 00:04:41.740
They are broken things upon the doorstep of salvation.

51
00:04:42.660 --> 00:04:47.900
Viridian's breath is a shallow rasp, each one a small victory.

52
00:04:48.860 --> 00:04:55.620
But there, etched into the living rock, is the gateway, the shrine of Ethelgard.

53
00:04:56.340 --> 00:05:02.540
Its light is not of the sun or moon, but something older, something gentle.

54
00:05:02.540 --> 00:05:08.940
It spills out like liquid hope, offering warmth after the wind's cruel bite.

55
00:05:09.480 --> 00:05:12.700
They have crossed the threshold of the world.

56
00:05:13.620 --> 00:05:17.020
Now, they must cross the last few feet.

57
00:05:17.520 --> 00:05:27.940
The air hums with a power that has slept for ages. The water is not merely water. It is the mountains pulse,

58
00:05:28.900 --> 00:05:38.020
the raw healing essence of the earth. Viridian lowers his weary head, and the moment his snout touches

59
00:05:38.020 --> 00:05:47.240
the surface, the mountain awakens for him. Light surges, not as an attack, but as a homecoming.

60
00:05:48.060 --> 00:05:56.300
The grey, the sickness, the fever, it is scoured away by a tide of pure, verdant life.

61
00:05:57.240 --> 00:06:03.260
The scales drink in the light, remembering their true name, Emerald.

62
00:06:03.760 --> 00:06:09.160
And then they fly, not a labored, desperate flap,

63
00:06:09.680 --> 00:06:16.240
but a powerful joyous stroke of wings that shatters the last of the storm's gloom.

64
00:06:17.080 --> 00:06:24.860
Viridian is himself again, a creature of emerald and sky, his roar, a peel of thunder that echoes

65
00:06:24.860 --> 00:06:33.000
not with sickness, but with life. Kalen, his rider, his partner, leans into the wind,

66
00:06:33.000 --> 00:06:36.380
her heart soaring as high as the mountain they conquered.

67
00:06:37.200 --> 00:06:44.580
Behind them lies a shrine to forgotten power, before them lies the whole world reclaimed.

68
00:06:45.440 --> 00:06:50.680
They are dragon and rider, they are healed, they are home.
